My meme

  • Below is the meme I have made for Project 1, inspired by the uphill battle I climb with technology. I have used an existing meme format but changed the context by adding a relatable situation for anyone who has had to use Rstudio for the first time at university.

library(magick)

# 1st square - create and label black square, adjust dimensions and add text
black_square_no <- image_blank(width = 300,
                             height = 200,
                             color = ("#000000")) %>%
 image_annotate(text = "Getting stuck\nusing Rstudio\nand giving up",
                color = ("#ffffff"),
                size = 40,
                font = "fairplay display",
                gravity = "north")

# 2nd square - label image and resize it
drake_no <- image_read("https://realworldmusictheory.com/content/images/2021/01/6e52acce958795508a7ecbf6a3656c0190-11-drake-hotline-bling.2x.rhorizontal.w700.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(300)

# 3rd square - create and label black square, adjust dimensions and ad text
black_square_yes <- image_blank(width = 300,
                             height = 170,
                             color = ("#000000")) %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Going to\nlab sessions\nfor help",
                 color = ("#ffffff"),
                 size = 40,
                 font = "fairplay display",
                 gravity = "north")

# label image and resize it
drake_yes <- image_read("https://i.cbc.ca/1.3279853.1532811524!/fileImage/httpImage/image.jpg_gen/derivatives/16x9_780/drake.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(300)


# create and label vector, combining drake no with black square no
top_line <- image_append(c(drake_no, black_square_no))

# create and label vector, combining drake yes with black square yes
bottom_line <- image_append(c(drake_yes, black_square_yes))

# create and label meme vector, combing previous two vectors and scale
meme <- c(top_line, bottom_line) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE) %>%
  image_scale(800)

# run the completed meme
#meme

# save meme to computer
image_write(meme, "statsmeme.png")

My animated GIF

  • Below is my animated GIF I have made, which I created for my sister, whoâ€™s birthday was on the day I started the assignment.

library(magick)

# making a birthday gif

# create each frame - label and attach background image, add text and adjust specs
frame_happy <- image_read("https://t4.ftcdn.net/jpg/05/05/29/59/360_F_505295990_agboeL7srxeFgudlWGbUEILA8OY88KRK.jpg") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Happy",
                 size = 40,
                 color = "#444876",
                 gravity = "west")

frame_birthday <- image_read("https://t4.ftcdn.net/jpg/05/05/29/59/360_F_505295990_agboeL7srxeFgudlWGbUEILA8OY88KRK.jpg") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Happy Birthday",
                 size = 40,
                 color = "#444876",
                 gravity = "west")

frame_to <- image_read("https://t4.ftcdn.net/jpg/05/05/29/59/360_F_505295990_agboeL7srxeFgudlWGbUEILA8OY88KRK.jpg") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Happy Birthday To",
                 size = 40,
                 color = "#444876",
                 gravity = "west")

frame_you <- image_read("https://t4.ftcdn.net/jpg/05/05/29/59/360_F_505295990_agboeL7srxeFgudlWGbUEILA8OY88KRK.jpg") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Happy Birthday To You",
                 size = 40,
                 color = "#444876",
                 gravity = "west")

frame_blank <- image_read("https://t4.ftcdn.net/jpg/05/05/29/59/360_F_505295990_agboeL7srxeFgudlWGbUEILA8OY88KRK.jpg")


frame_dear <- image_read("https://t4.ftcdn.net/jpg/05/05/29/59/360_F_505295990_agboeL7srxeFgudlWGbUEILA8OY88KRK.jpg") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Happy Birthday Dear",
                 size = 40,
                 color = "#444876",
                 gravity = "west")

frame_sinead <- image_read("https://t4.ftcdn.net/jpg/05/05/29/59/360_F_505295990_agboeL7srxeFgudlWGbUEILA8OY88KRK.jpg") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Happy Birthday Dear Sinead",
                 size = 40,
                 color = "#444876",
                 gravity = "west")

frame_big_you <- image_read("https://t4.ftcdn.net/jpg/05/05/29/59/360_F_505295990_agboeL7srxeFgudlWGbUEILA8OY88KRK.jpg") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Happy Birthday To YOU!",
                 size = 40,
                 color = "#444876",
                 gravity = "west")

frame_final <- image_read("https://berkscountyliving.com/downloads/18196/download/iStock-918933880.jpg?cb=1155e4a7652ab617e102986ad35ab972") %>%
  image_scale(540)
                 
# create a vector to order the frames
birthday_vector <- c(frame_happy, frame_birthday, frame_to, frame_you, frame_blank, frame_happy, frame_birthday, frame_to, frame_you, frame_blank, frame_happy, frame_birthday, frame_dear, frame_sinead, frame_blank, frame_happy, frame_birthday, frame_to, frame_big_you, frame_final, frame_final, frame_final)

# animate the frames and add frame per second rate
animation <- image_animate(birthday_vector, fps = 4)

image_write(animation, "animation.gif")
